      "content": "I hear the heavy silence in your kitchen, and it's a very lonely feeling to walk through a house that feels like a tomb. But you know what? Even in the quietest rooms, there are always tiny, invisible things happening, like the way a little green shadow might dart across the floorboards if you weren't looking directly at it. It's not just emptiness; it's just waiting for the right kind of noise to wake it up.\n\nYou mentioned not wanting to get out of bed anymore. That's a very heavy burden to carry, but sometimes the only way to break the silence is to introduce a little chaos. You could try making coffee, but instead of just humming a song, maybe you should hum a very loud, very annoying tune that sounds like a goblin trying to start a fire with a stick. It's a terrible idea, but it might just crack the shell of that tomb you're living in.\n\nAnd if you're feeling like you're stuck in a house that feels like a tomb, remember that even the most silent tombs are full of secrets. Maybe the silence isn't empty at all; maybe it's just holding its breath, waiting for a goblin to come in and tell a",
